{"title_page": "Fulham Cemetery", "text_new": "{{For|the Jewish cemetery |Fulham Road Jewish Cemetery}}\n{{For|Fulham New Cemetery |North Sheen Cemetery}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2016}}\n{{Use British English|date=June 2016}}\n{{Infobox cemetery\n| name        = Fulham Cemetery\n| image       = Fulham Palace Road Cemetery, Chapel doorway - geograph.org.uk - 1039597.jpg\n| imagesize   = \n| caption     = Fulham Cemetery chapel doorway\n| map_type    = \n| map_size    = \n| map_caption = \n| established =  1 August 1865 (date of consecration)<ref name = \"Mellor 155\"/>\n| country     = [[England]]\n| location    = [[Fulham Palace]] Road, [[London Borough of Hammersmith and Fulham]]\n| coordinates = {{coord|51|28|49|N|0|13|00|W|type:landmark_region:GB|display=inline,title}}\n| latitude    = \n| longitude   = \n| type        = \n| style       = \n| owner       = [[Hammersmith and Fulham Borough Council]]\n| size        = 13 acres<ref name = \"Mellor 155\">Meller, Hugh; Parsons, Brian (2011). ''London Cemeteries: An Illustrated Guide and Gazetteer'' (Fifth ed.). [[Stroud, Gloucestershire]]: [[The History Press]]. p. 155. {{ISBN|978 0 7524 6183 0}}.</ref> \n| graves      = \n| interments  = \n| website     = [https://www.lbhf.gov.uk/births-deaths-and-marriages/deaths/cemeteries-and-burials/cemeteries-hammersmith-fulham/ Official website]\n| findagraveid= 2249695\n}}\n'''Fulham Cemetery''', also known as '''Fulham Old Cemetery'''<ref name=\"H&F\">{{cite web | url=https://www.lbhf.gov.uk/births-deaths-and-marriages/deaths/cemeteries-and-burials/cemeteries-hammersmith-fulham | title=Fulham and Margravine Cemeteries | publisher=[[London Borough of Hammersmith and Fulham]] | work=Cemeteries in Hammersmith & Fulham | accessdate=19 June 2016}}</ref> and as '''Fulham Palace Road Cemetery''',<ref name=\"Gardens\">{{cite web | url=http://www.londongardensonline.org.uk/gardens-online-record.asp?ID=HAF017 | title=Fulham Palace Road Cemetery | publisher=[[London Parks & Gardens Trust]] | work=London Gardens Online | accessdate=19 June 2016}}</ref> is in the [[London Borough of Hammersmith and Fulham]], just off [[Fulham Palace]] Road. Designed by John Hall, it opened in 1865.<ref name=\"Gardens\"/> The closest [[London Underground]] station is [[Barons Court tube station|Barons Court]].\n\n==Notable burials==\n[[File:Fulham Palace Road Cemetery 20190426 122301 (47704487321).jpg|thumb|The cemetery]]\n[[File:Fulham Cemetery (geograph 2304435).jpg|thumb|Another view of the cemetery]]\n*Lieutenant-General [[Burke Cuppage| Sir Burke Douglas Cuppage]] KCB (1794\u20131877), [[Lieutenant-Governor of Jersey]] 1863\u201368.<ref name = \"Mellor 156\">Meller, Hugh; Parsons, Brian (2011). ''London Cemeteries: An Illustrated Guide and Gazetteer'' (Fifth ed.). [[Stroud, Gloucestershire]]: [[The History Press]]. p. 156. {{ISBN|978 0 7524 6183 0}}.</ref>  \n\nThe cemetery contains the [[Commonwealth War Graves Commission|war graves]] of 238 Commonwealth service personnel, 179 from [[World War I]] of whom seven are commemorated by a special memorial headstone, and 57 from [[World War II]]. Those whose graves have no headstones are listed by name on a screen wall memorial in the main war graves plot.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.cwgc.org/find-a-cemetery/cemetery/2043510/FULHAM%20(PALACE%20ROAD)%20CEMETERY/|title=Fulham Palace Road Cemetery|publisher=[[Commonwealth War Graves Commission]]|access-date= 21 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[Fulham Road Jewish Cemetery]], Jewish Cemetery on Fulham Road\n* [[North Sheen Cemetery]], also known as Fulham New Cemetery\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://www.lbhf.gov.uk/births-deaths-and-marriages/deaths/cemeteries-and-burials/cemeteries-hammersmith-fulham/ Official website]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Fulham Cemetery}}\n[[Category:1865 establishments in England]]\n[[Category:Buildings and structures in the London Borough of Hammersmith and Fulham]]\n[[Category:Cemeteries in London]]\n[[Category:Commonwealth War Graves Commission cemeteries in England]]\n[[Category:Fulham]]\n[[Category:Hammersmith and Fulham cemeteries]]\n[[Category:World War I memorials in the United Kingdom]]\n\n{{UK-cemetery-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{For|the Jewish cemetery |Fulham Road Jewish Cemetery}}\n{{For|Fulham New Cemetery |North Sheen Cemetery}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2016}}\n{{Use British English|date=June 2016}}\n{{Infobox cemetery\n| name        = Fulham Cemetery\n| image       = Fulham Palace Road Cemetery, Chapel doorway - geograph.org.uk - 1039597.jpg\n| imagesize   = \n| caption     = Fulham Cemetery chapel doorway\n| map_type    = \n| map_size    = \n| map_caption = \n| established =  1 August 1865 (date of consecration)<ref name = \"Mellor 155\"/>\n| country     = [[England]]\n| location    = [[Fulham Palace]] Road, [[London Borough of Hammersmith and Fulham]]\n| coordinates = {{coord|51|28|49|N|0|13|00|W|type:landmark_region:GB|display=inline,title}}\n| latitude    = \n| longitude   = \n| type        = \n| style       = \n| owner       = [[Hammersmith and Fulham Borough Council]]\n| size        = 13 acres<ref name = \"Mellor 155\">Meller, Hugh; Parsons, Brian (2011). ''London Cemeteries: An Illustrated Guide and Gazetteer'' (Fifth ed.). [[Stroud, Gloucestershire]]: [[The History Press]]. p. 155. {{ISBN|978 0 7524 6183 0}}.</ref> \n| graves      = \n| interments  = \n| website     = [https://www.lbhf.gov.uk/births-deaths-and-marriages/deaths/cemeteries-and-burials/cemeteries-hammersmith-fulham/ Official website]\n| findagraveid= 2249695\n}}\n'''Fulham Cemetery''', also known as '''Fulham Old Cemetery'''<ref name=\"H&F\">{{cite web | url=https://www.lbhf.gov.uk/births-deaths-and-marriages/deaths/cemeteries-and-burials/cemeteries-hammersmith-fulham | title=Fulham and Margravine Cemeteries | publisher=[[London Borough of Hammersmith and Fulham]] | work=Cemeteries in Hammersmith & Fulham | accessdate=19 June 2016}}</ref> and as '''Fulham Palace Road Cemetery''',<ref name=\"Gardens\">{{cite web | url=http://www.londongardensonline.org.uk/gardens-online-record.asp?ID=HAF017 | title=Fulham Palace Road Cemetery | publisher=[[London Parks & Gardens Trust]] | work=London Gardens Online | accessdate=19 June 2016}}</ref> is in the [[London Borough of Hammersmith and Fulham]], just off [[Fulham Palace]] Road. Designed by John Hall, it opened in 1865.<ref name=\"Gardens\"/> The closest [[London Underground]] station is [[Barons Court tube station|Barons Court]].\n\n==Notable burials==\n[[File:Fulham Palace Road Cemetery 20190426 122301 (47704487321).jpg|thumb|The cemetery]]\n[[File:Fulham Cemetery (geograph 2304435).jpg|thumb|Another view of the cemetery]]\n*[[Burke Cuppage|Lieutenant-General Sir Burke Douglas Cuppage]] KCB (1794\u20131877), [[Lieutenant-Governor of Jersey]] 1863\u201368.<ref name = \"Mellor 156\">Meller, Hugh; Parsons, Brian (2011). ''London Cemeteries: An Illustrated Guide and Gazetteer'' (Fifth ed.). [[Stroud, Gloucestershire]]: [[The History Press]]. p. 156. {{ISBN|978 0 7524 6183 0}}.</ref>  \n\nThe cemetery contains the [[Commonwealth War Graves Commission|war graves]] of 238 Commonwealth service personnel, 179 from [[World War I]] of whom seven are commemorated by a special memorial headstone, and 57 from [[World War II]]. Those whose graves have no headstones are listed by name on a screen wall memorial in the main war graves plot.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.cwgc.org/find-a-cemetery/cemetery/2043510/FULHAM%20(PALACE%20ROAD)%20CEMETERY/|title=Fulham Palace Road Cemetery|publisher=[[Commonwealth War Graves Commission]]|access-date= 21 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[Fulham Road Jewish Cemetery]], Jewish Cemetery on Fulham Road\n* [[North Sheen Cemetery]], also known as Fulham New Cemetery\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://www.lbhf.gov.uk/births-deaths-and-marriages/deaths/cemeteries-and-burials/cemeteries-hammersmith-fulham/ Official website]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Fulham Cemetery}}\